message.content: cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SYNN - The paper discusses the training of a spiking neural network on analog neuromorphic hardware, which falls under the category of neural networks and their applications (cs.NE). The use of hardware for training and the focus on energy consumption and speed suggest that the paper could also be classified under the sub-categories of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET) and systems and control (cs.SYNN). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and backpropagation, which are relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
